Review: Tea and Cookies are worth of money, the sugar is kept seperate. The staff service is quick. They have wide varieties of snacks and pastries also. Its in the Bangalore International Terminal in between Gate No. 39 & 40.  Near to it there is lot of sitting space to relax and enjoy the break before flight.

This is one of the eateries in the ground level of Kempegowda International Airport, Bangalore.  They have snacks, bakery products and other dishes for breakfast, lunch and dinner.  The place is neat and elegant with less crowd.  Service is friendly.  I enjoyed filter coffee.

Located inside the bangalore international airport, this food outlet is near to gate 3 and has to come down from the main terminal to be reached. It's a decent food outlet and mainly serves baked items, juices and other beverages. They have few seating table in front of the store too.

This is very near to Gate 40.  They have varieties of breads, cappuccino, latte and our indian filter coffee,.donuts. Pastries, Sandwich etc.  They also have all aerated drinks.  Good service by the staff. They also sell organic coffee powder.  Had vegetarian puff and coffee ans they were good.

Those familiar with the layout of Bangalore International Airport, they would know that gates 3 to 11 are located on the ground floor, with an escalator. Urban food Market basically serves bakery items such as croissants, sandwiches, cookies etc. It also serves coffee. There is no difference in prices as compared to other similar joints, but it definitely offers convenience for fliers during their waiting time. One interesting thing is that it offers take-away, which is actually a substitute for costly on-board meals.

The food is of best quality. Very well behaved staffs. Remembering that you're in the airport the food is value for money! I'd recommend this place.

On the 24th of April 19 at about 130 I at the ground floor of Bangalore Internatoonal Airport (KIA)in Urban Food market  I ordered for a cappuccino,  which is priced at Rs. 129, the lady at the counter said it is Rs.130. I paid by my debit card, and later after after boarding the flight  I noticed that my card was swiped for a wapping Rs. 1300, instead of Rs. 130. Lodged a complaint yet no response.  I condemn the said act. The organisation should  stand up to address the grievances.

All in all for good early morning kick.
